issue.title: Integrate web backend.
issue.body: Retrofit and stuff. You probably know the drill. Talk to the web people.

issue.title: Make it pretty.
issue.body:
- Polish UI for improved demo quality.
- Create presentation for judges.
- Make UI consistent with web client.

issue.title: Create depth prediction algorithm.
issue.body:
Slack contains resources that describe existing algorithms. 
- Doesn't have to be perfect, average of depth maps should counter some error. 
- Implement some (basic) machine learning and export results to csv, json, etc.
  - Makes algorithm self improving throughout the hackathon
  - Cool talking point, especially if mesh results are rough in demo ("It doesn't look very good right now, but our algorithm implements machine learning that becomes increasingly aware of depth features by doing a fancy thing...")
  - Make machine learning easy to exclude from processing in case of excessive computation time

issue.title: Create STL file programatically.
issue.body: Figure out how to create the file from a set of coordinates. Mesh has to be generated in a particular order.

issue.title: Create UI.
issue.body:
# Entry Point
- Logged in already? [MVP 0.1]
  - Library of locally saved models
  - Floating action button to create new mesh
  - Navigation drawer for user details, app settings, online content portal
- Not logged in? [MVP 1.0]
  
  -- Go to login screen (or generate sample models [MVP 2.0])
# New Mesh Screen
- Can be forced horizontal if picture is taken horizontally
- 5 or 6 boxes
  - Each box represents a side
  - Clicking a box takes you to the picture taking activity
  - Boxes labeled, indicate image taken (show preview of image [MVP 1.0]
  - User controls mesh detail
  - Set box side length [MVP 1.0]

|  | Top |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Left | Front | Right | Back |
|  | Bottom |  |  |
# Picture taking
- Horizontal probably
- Most of screen is camera
- Take picture button
- Confirm picture [MVP 0.1]
- Request redo if image is bad [MVP 2.0]
- Has rectangular overlay that defines the back of the box
  - User adjusts with sliders [MVP 0.1]
# Display result of mesh
- Can be done in OpenGL pretty easily, mostly from sample code
  - There may be a library that can display mesh
- Absolutely necessary, too hard to demo realtime mesh gen

issue.title: Generate mesh from images.
issue.body:
# Generate 3D mesh
## Basic mesh

Surface is defined by a continuous surface of triangles.
Make resolution scalable - specify the max number of triangles in the mesh.
## MVP Requirements:
## 5 images
#### Front, Back, Left, Right Images

Create the general shape from the sides of the object.
#### Top Image

Allows for more accurate mapping of the surface texture on the mesh created by the side images.
# Bonus
#### Take a bottom image to create a true to form 3D model for objects that aren't flat on the bottom.
